        <h4>A solid contender</h4>
        <p>After reading this <%= link_to "Zagat list", "https://www.zagat.com/b/houston/8-places-to-get-your-ramen-fix-in-houston#3" %> I decided to give <%= link_to "Ramen Jin", "https://www.facebook.com/ramenjin/" %> a try. They have several varieties of Ramen and I chose the Tonkotsu Shoyu. Everybody has different preferences in what they like about Ramen.  I prefer chewy noodles (al dente if we were eating Italian) and a hearty broth. I was very satisfied with the Tonkotsu Shoyu and I have returned several times since. The egg was soft boiled to a nice consistency.  They added corn to the soup, which I wouldn't normally ask for, but it worked out OK.</p>
