        <h4>Best Atmosphere?</h4>
        <p><%= link_to "Nippon Japanese Restaurant", "http://nippon-sushi.com" %> advertises themselves as the "only Japanese Restaurant that specialize in true Japanese food in Houston." It can be a bit confusing figuring out where to park because I always want to turn into the parking lot next door, but once inside you're in for a treat. This restaurant feels authentic to me because it doesn't have that modern feel most newer Japanese restaurants have. I came here for lunch one day to try their ramen and accidently ordered the Miso Ramen. Even though I'm not the biggest fan of large quantities of miso broth, I would try it again.</p>
