        <h4>Best Broth</h4>
        <p>Perhaps the newest establishment among this list, <%= link_to "Jinya Ramen Bar", "http://jinya-ramenbar.com/" %> is located south of downtown almost where the edge of Midtown meets the Montrose district. I've tried several of their ramen varieties and I'm in love with the Tonkotsu Black. It has a nice meaty broth that doesn't disappoint. If pork isn't your thing then they also have a good selection of delicious chicken-based ramen. You know it's good when the only negative thing I can say is that eating a whole egg with chopsticks is clumsy (most ramen preparations have the egg already cut in half). This place gets cboxded on the weekends, especially for dinner. It's the real deal.</p>
